(firstQuint)The Efficacy and Safety of Prophylactic Central Lymph Node Dissection in Papillary Thyroid Carcinoma.

 The aim of this study is to investigate the efficacy and safety of prophylactic central lymph node dissection in papillary thyroid carcinoma.

 Primary outcome is the structural recurrence rate.

 Secondary outcomes are operative time, postoperative complications, and quality of life.

 The enrolled patients were randomly assigned to control group and intervention group (1:1 allocation).

